Their brand name is one of the most powerful in the world of football and recent TV figures have reiterated their superiority, with it revealed that Real Madrid were last season’s most watched Spanish team. Los Blancos counted on 136.69 million viewers, trailed by their domestic rivals Barcelona, who were watched by 108.79 million.This is according to a study by Havas Sports, which was reported on Palco23. Sevilla and Atletico Madrid follow with just over 40 million viewers, less than a third of Los Blancos’ numbers.Real Madrid led in the Champions League and LaLiga figures, while the Blaugrana were the most-viewed team in the Copa del Rey, having gone all the way to the final. Finally, the most-watched game of the season was the European final between Real Madrid and Liverpool, followed by more than 9.29 million people.